Ever think that a policy your school impliments is unfair and dealing with freedom of speech? Such as getting things cut from the newspaper or magazines because of "obsene" subjects? Here is some help.
 
http://splc.org/
 
If you go there it tells a lot about things, and you can even request information on a specific thing if you're unsure. AND search the site for previous cases.
 
I'm bringing this up because there was an issue with our newspaper and literary annual about things getting cut. But we're getting a lawyer from the site to fight for us next year on things like that. Our Junior class might not have a prom next year because we don't have the funding, for evil reasons that piss me off, but i'm not allowed to talk about because it's "mean" so it got cut. So no one will know we need help because our AP won't let us print the newspaper with the article in it.
 
It makes me wanna gag. I feel like punching the bitch. So anyway, i'm gonna run for Senior Class President next year and work my butt off to get a new sponser for us and raise money so we can have a prom. Thought i would share.

I think i need people too much.  I think i try so hard to stay away from others because i know it.  I hate when someone comes around and thinks that they can help me.  They try so hard i begin to believe it.  But even though i know they can't, i'm still wishing.

Stephen was an example.  He believed all that he said he felt.  He was really messed up and he had issues.  The whole time i tried to help him.. and even though things were really bad, i still thought he'd save me.

I find i put up a really big wall between myself and the rest of the world.  I've stopped peeking around to see who is trying to come in and just tell them to fuck off.  People tell me i have to stop being so protective.  They ask me what i'm afraid of.  To be honest, i'm not sure i'm afraid.  I'm just tired of trying and trying and getting nowhere at all.  After so many years of putting up a house just to have someone come and knock it down like the big bad wolf, i've decided to turn around and walk the other way.  So maybe i'll be alone, and maybe i'm never going to be happy, but i'd rather not suffer and watch the rest of the world laugh at my misery. 

Every REAL friend i find i have, something makes it hard.  First it was Rachael.  My dear, fucked up friend.  I blame her for stealing my innocence.  I was a good child.  I really was.  But somehow, her twisted ways got me all spun up and i forgot what i was doing.  I ended up getting away from her though.  I found my place, maybe a little too late, but i did.  I ended up trying to save her.  I tried so hard, but it didn't really matter.  She didn't care where she was headed, she just wanted to get away.  She got messed up and she drug me along with her for a bit.  A few years later she found herself someone that was never really there for her; God.  I saved her life and she thanks him.  She thinks she made it on her own and she didn't.  Some day she'll some to her senses, i hope. And then there was Bethany.  Now i'm not sure exactly what went wrong there, but in the end it doesn't matter.  I've gotten beyond it, and she still has this issue with me.  I really do wonder when she is going to grow up.  I'd have thought the "war" would be over by now.  With Kay, we both had our problems.  Neither of us had the ability to fix the other but damnit we tried. And sometimes we would get so angry that we couldn't piece each other together we hated ourselves and each other.  We'd take it out on each other when we'd noticed we failed.  Life happened somewhere between then and now, and we're so far apart.  We still talk sometimes.  But nothing is ever going to be the same.  It's funny how when you're in middle school, you're so naive.  I thought we'd be best friends forever.  I knew we'd have our problems, but that didn't stop me from dreaming that when we're old and dying, we'd still be friends.  I still thought that on our death beds we'd be staying up all night listening to our crazy dreams... So after all that and a year later, i had Kevin.  Now i really and truely believe that with him i was going to be somebody.  Things were as perfect as i'd ever seen them be.  I was laughing and happy and i felt like i was flying.  But then, we also went our seperate ways.  I was still holding on because i didn't want to say good-bye.  I don't know if i ever meant anything to him because he didn't even fight for me.  He let go and turned around without ever looking back.  I was sad at first.  I'd cried for days and hadn't slept for nights at a time.  After i stopped crying and hurting from trying not to cry at school, and people telling me that i'd be okay.  I got pissed off. I got so angry i thought i would kill him if i ever saw him again.  And then, i talked myself into forgetting about him and moving on.  But part of me never really bounced back.  Little by little the light in my eyes turned dark.  All i know, is if i ever see him again, he's going to hear a lot from me.  But if he's smart, he'll keep his distance.  Of course his little brother, Daniel, looks just like him..  I see him in school all the time.  Every time i see him i see Kevin.  And i get angry all over again.  I'm not sure if his brother knows what happened because he still says hi..  But i was happy.. i really was.

                    ---<33Kris+

So, on thursday i had my weekly meeting for the Literary Annual. As you can imagine, we had quite a few submissions once again. I submitted a new one of my own, which is just below this entry. I think i got 5-5-5-4-4 as my rating, 5 being the best. Needless to say i was happy. 

Being the editor, i told Burke i would take the stuff home and type it up, which is what he was having me attempt to do in a half hour getting told to get off of the computers every 5 minutes because they were shutting down. It was getting a bit rediculous. I was like "listen Burke, i could take this stuff home and knock it all out by Monday." So finally after about two meetings he gave in. And what happened this weekend, that usually doesn't happen? Well, for one, i got overloaded with homework, which i didn't do, and my parents were all on my case about getting the bathroom and my bed room cleaned. I told my mother i wanted to relax friday night because i just got home from school and i was tired.

Well, Sat. morning rolls around and i'm still being lazy. So i dit down at my computer and type up a bunch of the poems. I'm still going but when i try to save the one, it said there was no more disk space left. Well i opened it up and bam, there are 5 digi cam original sized pictures, a web document and something else. Well he had 2004-2005 Literary Annual written on the front of the disk so i figured, why not, i'll just delete them. I hope he didn't need them for anything :\ lolz 

So anyway, i did that until i got hungry and smelt the pancakes. Went downstairs to eat and well, i did. Yummy. So my parents decide they are going to get out of the house for the day. But need i remind you, they were still angry about the bathroom. So they told me that it better be spotless when they return home "or else". Well, you know, i'm not too bright, but that didn't sound very good. So of course i went straight to it. Well, i have very low tolerence for other people's messes. So add the usual bathroom mess and smells and you've got yourself a party. One that i ripped up my invitation for a long time ago. 

Three hours and 10 attempted puke sessions later i was finished. All i wanted to do was take a shower. No such luck. My sister ended up taking a bath right after i was finished so i'd had to wait for her to get done and then wait an hour for the water to come back [it's a huge tub, whirl pool jacuzzi style!]. So i waited. Then my parents came home. How fun, right? They asked about the bathroom and i told him it was clean and blah blah blah. But then comes another fun chore. I had to help wash all four dogs that are about half my size and weight, and lets just say i'm not on the light side of the scale.

After that was finished i was too tired to even stand. So i laid down on my bed under the fan to cool off and relax. Well being my tired self, i passed out and took about a 4 hour nap. I was all refreshed and such. And then i just felt like relaxing the rest of the weekend which was a bad idea. I forgot to do my homework and clean my room. But i read, and i started my letter to Morgan. I dunno, i guess all in all this weekend was pretty productive. whoa big word!

Oh and i forgot to mention, i got some funny pictures of my dog.. heh, i'll share later.

Beautiful Like Me

what's wrong with the world
minds of the once caring
brainwashed by the t.v.
are happy to kill
as a reward for their efforts
efforts to maintain "freedom"
these people live in ignorance
a life of pure bliss
while day by day
i slowly lose my faith
in the human race
the rich sit at home
sipping their expensive tea
whist the poor sleep alone
on a snowy park bench
starving for the tiniest bit of food
when their sweetest memory
is of their last bite
of a warm homemade meal
when girls go anorexic 
to be like the models on t.v
just because 5'11 and 120lbs
became the idealistic body
But who wants to be skin and bones
Who wants to be plastic-like fake
I'm full-figured and proud
Because i'm not beautiful like you
I'm beautiful like me.

You Know You're From Maryland When...
You know more than 10 people who own boats and they all park them at the same marina in Annapolis You can pronounce and spell "Pocomoke," "Mattaponi," "Accokeek," and "Havre de Grace" You prononce "Bowie" BOO-ie not BOW-ie or BAUW-ie 1 hour is an easy commute to work You have more than three recipies for crabcakes French fries just don't taste right without Old Bay There are more than two crab places in your town Even your high school cafeteria made good crabcakes You got your first lacrosse stick before you were six years old You call all turtles "terrapins" You refer to your state as "Merlind" Your mother shops at Hecht's You still call Six Flags America "Adventure World", or even "Wild World" You still remember the Wild World commercial (Wild World's the cure for the summertime blues!) You can tell the difference between the smells of septic and marsh. You not only know how to eat hard crabs but you also know how to catch them, cook them and tell the males from the females. You don't think that Assawoman Bay is a strange name for a body of water. You know perfectly well why Rehoboth is called "Little San Francisco" M R Ducks makes perfect sense. So does C M Wangs. You think Salisbury is a big city. You think of dumplings as wet slippery squares of boiled dough. You and your boss take off of work when the fish are running or the ducks are flying in. You've eaten muskrat at a church dinner but think it's better the way you fix it. You think of "Dairy Queen" as a pageant title and not a place to get an ice cream. "Formal wear" is a ball cap, a flannel shirt and Timberlands. You still root for the Orioles even when they suck You'll never understand why tourists come to DC. When in Florida, you can only laugh when you see signs saying "Real Maryland Blue Crab Cakes!" You color with "Crowns", take a "Share" with "Wooter" and think the president lives in "Warshenton." You know the difference between Glen Burnie ghetto and Catonsville ghetto. Your whole family lives within a 200 mile radius of your town. Dale Earnhardt's accident was a close personal loss to your father At least one man in your family is a waterman You plan for "The Festival" a year in advance. During the summer, you spend more time in Ocean City than at home. Margret Heater, Hedspace, Jepetto, Outside Joke and Mary Prankster are people you think are "Famous" Your radio dial is stuck on 99.1 You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends from Maryland.

    I'm not sure if i'll ever TRUST them, but i can just have fun with them and that's something that will never get old. I can find other people that i can trust who will be there for me someday.
